content.text:
In this experiment, you will see some words, 
separated by #####.

When you see the word, 
your job is to say whether it is something 
natural or man-made.

Press any key to continue...

Natural could be things like plants, animals, rocks.. 
anything from the natural world.

Man-made refers to anything produced by people: 
objects, tools, machines.. 
anything that requires a person to make it.

Press any key to continue...

Try to respond as quickly and accurately as you can.

You need to respond within two seconds.

Sometimes, you will make a mistake. 
That's ok. 

Sometimes, you might be unsure what the word means. 
That's ok too.

Just go on to the next one.

Press any key to continue...

The whole experiment will take you around 
6-7 minutes to complete.

There is a break when you are halfway through.

Press any key to continue...

Practice complete!

Now you are ready to start the real experiment.

Remember to answer as quickly as you can, 
as you only have two seconds to respond.

Enjoy!

Press any key to begin..

Break time!

If this is the first time you see this screen,
take a quick break, and press the
space key
when you are ready to continue.

If this is the second time you see this screen,
you're done!
Press the space key to end the experiment.

Before you start the real experiment, 
there is a quick practice round.

Remember:

press "n" if the word is something natural

press "m" if the word is something man-made

Press SPACE to start the practice round...

When you see the word,

press the "n" key if it is natural.

press the "m" key if it is man-made.


Press any key to continue...

Break time!

If this is the first time you see this screen,
take a quick break, and press the
space key
when you are ready to continue.

If this is the second time you see this screen,
you're done!
Press the space key to end the experiment.
